-- India’s Prithviraj Chavan to Be Maharashtra’s New Chief Minister
-- B y   B i b h u d a t t a   P r a d h a n
-- 2010-11-10T04:54:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-10/prithviraj-chavan-to-be-maharashtra-s-new-chief-minister-mukherjee-says.html
India’s federal Science and
Technology Minister  Prithviraj Chavan  will be the next chief
minister of the western state of  Maharashtra , home to the
financial capital of Mumbai and the headquarters of the Tata
Group and Reliance Industries Ltd.  Chavan will succeed  Ashok Chavan , who resigned yesterday.
Congress Party General Secretary Janardhan Dwivedi said Ashok
Chavan had been asked by party chief  Sonia Gandhi  to step down,
“pending enquiry” into an alleged housing scandal.  Gandhi picked Prithviraj Chavan for the post, Finance
Minister  Pranab Mukherjee  told reporters in New Delhi today.
Congress leads coalition governments at both the state and
federal level.  To contact the reporter on this story:
